reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Powerful and Versatile: USB C Fast Charger with 100W GaN Technology
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded to the USB C Fast Charger with 100W GaN technology and it has transformed the way I charge my devices. This charger has quickly become an essential part of my daily routine.Pros:1. **Remarkable Charging Speed**: With 100W of power, this charger is lightning-fast. It charges my devices at impressive speeds, saving me valuable time.2. **Versatility**: The six ports offer exceptional versatility. I can charge multiple devices simultaneously, including laptops, tablets, smartphones, and more, without compromising on charging speed.3. **GaN Technology**: GaN (Gallium Nitride) technology is a game-changer. It allows for a more compact design without sacrificing power, making this charger incredibly portable and efficient.4. **Sturdy Build**: The charger feels well-constructed and durable. It's designed to withstand daily use and wear and tear.5. **Safety Features**: The charger comes equipped with safety features like overcurrent protection and temperature control, providing peace of mind while charging expensive devices.In summary, the USB C Fast Charger with 100W GaN technology is a powerhouse charger that has simplified my device charging needs. Its impressive speed, versatility, and reliability make it a top choice for anyone with multiple devices to charge. Whether I'm at home or on the go, this charger ensures all my gadgets stay powered up efficiently.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Title: Efficient and Versatile USB C Fast Charger Power Strip for Multiple Devices
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the USB C Fast Charger, 100W GaN 6 Port Type USB C Charging Station Hub Block from Amazon, and it has proven to be an excellent investment for my charging needs. This charger offers impressive functionality, efficient charging speeds, and versatile compatibility, making it a reliable power strip for multiple devices.The standout feature of this charger is its GaN (Gallium Nitride) technology, which allows for efficient and compact power delivery. Despite its small size, the charger delivers an impressive 100W of power, making it capable of fast charging a wide range of devices, including iPad, iPhone 14, 13, 12, 11 Pro Max, Pixel, Note, and Galaxy devices.The six ports—three USB C and three USB A—provide ample connectivity options, allowing me to charge multiple devices simultaneously. This is particularly convenient when I have multiple gadgets that need charging, as it saves time and eliminates the need for multiple chargers or power outlets.The charging speed of this power strip is exceptional. Whether I’m charging my smartphone, tablet, or other USB-powered devices, it consistently delivers fast and reliable charging performance. I have noticed that my devices charge noticeably quicker compared to other chargers I’ve used in the past.The build quality of the charger is impressive. It feels solid and durable, giving me confidence in its longevity. The 5ft cord is of sufficient length, providing flexibility in positioning the charger to suit my needs.The versatility of this charger is another notable aspect. Its compatibility with a wide range of devices, including both USB C and USB A devices, makes it a practical choice for households with different gadgets. I appreciate the convenience of having multiple charging options in a single device.In terms of value for money, this USB C Fast Charger Power Strip delivers excellent bang for the buck. Its high-quality construction, efficient charging capabilities, and versatile compatibility make it a worthwhile investment.To sum it up, the USB C Fast Charger, 100W GaN 6 Port Type USB C Charging Station Hub Block is an exceptional power strip that meets all my charging needs. Its efficient charging speeds, versatile compatibility, and solid build quality make it an ideal choice for individuals who require fast and reliable charging for multiple devices. I highly recommend this charger to anyone seeking a convenient and efficient charging solution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very solidly built, but does not work with some charging cables.
reviews.reviewText: This is a very nicely built unit, it does not feel cheap at all and is a good value for the price. It has no issues charging multiple devices at once, but do pay attention to what ports share a charging circuit.I did have one significant issue with it, and that is it would not charge either of my Nintendo Switch controllers, one the official Pro controller and one an aftermarket. It turned out to be something with the USB-A to USB-C cables that came with each controller. When I used a regular USB-C cable, it worked. So this will charge Switch controllers, you will just need a different cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for some one who has to charge multiple devices
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased a USB hub with three USB A and three USB C ports, and overall, I'm very happy with my purchase. This hub has made it much easier for me to connect all of my devices to my computer, and I appreciate the fact that it has a mix of USB A and USB C ports.In terms of performance, the hub works well and I haven't experienced any issues with it. All of the ports seem to function properly, and I've been able to connect multiple devices at once without any issues.The only minor complaint I have about this hub is that the ports provide around 15% less power than advertised. This might be due to my setup, but I've noticed that some devices charge slightly slower than I expected when connected to this hub. However, this hasn't been a major issue for me, and the hub still provides enough power to charge my devices.Overall, I think this USB hub is a great product and I would definitely recommend it to others. The mix of USB A and USB C ports is a nice touch, and it has made it much easier for me to connect all of my devices to my computer. While the slightly lower power output is a minor downside, it hasn't affected my overall experience with the hub, and I still think it's a great product that's worth considering if you need more USB ports for your devices.
